https://imgur.com/2TXZNRa

At this stage, an additional server and a load balancer have been incorporated to efficiently distribute and manage traffic. The DNS directs traffic to the load balancer's IP address.

The load balancer's role is to evenly distribute incoming traffic between the two servers. This ensures balanced traffic handling.

When a single server encounters a sudden influx of traffic, the website crashes due to the infrastructure's restricted capacity to manage higher traffic volumes.
